torique, puis les thèmes du réductionnisme, de la complexité, des méthodes expérimentales. Il aborde ensuite les théories évolutionnistes et conclut sur l'interdisciplinarité. Un appel à l'interaction sciences-société termine le livre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aBiophysics. 4aLife sciences/Biology. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh1 aBornarel, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDebru, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacrot, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMache, Régis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPebay-Peyroula, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013z978311102411008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Backlist eBook Package 2001 - 2015z978311075641840uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-0136-740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759801367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9782759801367/original  a978-3-11-075641-8  EDP Sciences Backlist eBook Package 2001 - 2015c2001d2015  a978-3-11-102411-0  EDP Sciences Backlist eBook Package 2000-2013c2008d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK